  "description": "R5: `Person.photo`",
  "purpose": "This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the\r\nelement `Person.photo` as defined in FHIR R5\r\nin FHIR R4.\r\n\r\nThe source element is defined as:\r\n`Person.photo` 0..* `Attachment`\r\n\r\nAcross FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:\r\n*  R5: `Person.photo` 0..* `Attachment`\n*  R4B: `Person.photo` 0..1 `Attachment`\n*  R4: `Person.photo` 0..1 `Attachment`\r\n\r\nFollowing are the generation technical comments:\r\nElement `Person.photo` allows multiple values in the source, but is mapped to an element that does not allow multiple values in the target.\nElement `Person.photo` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Person.photo` as `SourceIsBroaderThanTarget`.",
